{"id":"schools-of-the-prophets","term":"Schools of the Prophets","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Samuel 19:18\">1 Sam. 19:18-24</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 2:3\">2 Kings 2:3</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 2:5\">5</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 2:7\">7</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 2:12\">12</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 2:15\">15</a>) were instituted for the purpose of training young men for the prophetical and priestly offices. (See PROPHET; SAMUEL.)</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Samuel 19:18","2 Kings 2:3","2 Kings 2:5","2 Kings 2:7","2 Kings 2:12","2 Kings 2:15"]}